edu.stanford.math.plex4.graph

Class UndirectedListGraph

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.stanford.math.plex4.graph.UndirectedListGraph
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AbstractUndirectedGraph, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Iterable<edu.stanford.math.primitivelib.autogen.pair.IntIntPair>

    public class UndirectedListGraph
extends java.lang.Object
implements AbstractUndirectedGraph
    This class implements the functionality of an undirected graph. It uses an adjacency list data structure. That is, for each vertex u, it stores the set of vertices {v_1, .., v_k} such that u is connected to v_i and v_i < u. For example consider the following graph: 0 -- 1 | | 2 -- 3 -- 4 The following storage scheme is used: 1: {0} 2: {0} 3: {1, 2} 4: {3}
    Author:
    Andrew Tausz
